<paragraph id="8BF9FF617C05CA69FC8BF8B92189FCF6" blockId="18.[827,1443,1805,1889]" lastBlockId="19.[145,761,705,850]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="239" pageId="18" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B93223737C05CA68FC8BF8B923BCF886" box="[827,986,1805,1826]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="238">Distribution:</emphasis>
Both species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C05CA68FB00F8B92531F886" authorityName="Slavenko &amp; Tamar &amp; Tallowin &amp; Kraus &amp; Allison &amp; Carranza &amp; Meiri" authorityYear="2022" box="[1200,1367,1805,1826]" class="Squamata" family="Scincidae" genus="Nubeoscincus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Reptilia" pageId="18" pageNumber="238" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93223737C05CA68FB00F8B92531F886" box="[1200,1367,1805,1826]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="238">Nubeoscincus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur at extremely high elevations from the western New 
<collectingCountry id="F351BFF17C05CA68FC8BF8FF23F6F8C5" box="[827,912,1867,1889]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="18" pageNumber="238">Guinea</collectingCountry>
Highlands to the western (Indonesian) parts of the island and are known from extremely limited distributions: 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C04CA69FE8BFD5521A0FD51" authorityName="Slavenko &amp; Tamar &amp; Tallowin &amp; Kraus &amp; Allison &amp; Carranza &amp; Meiri" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Slavenko &amp; Tamar &amp; Tallowin &amp; Kraus &amp; Allison &amp; Carranza &amp; Meiri" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[315,454,736,758]" class="Squamata" family="Scincidae" genus="Nubeoscincus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Reptilia" pageId="19" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis id="B93223737C04CA69FE8BFD552129FD52" box="[315,335,737,758]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="239">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B93223737C04CA69FED0FD5421A0FD51" box="[352,454,736,757]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="239">glacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
near Puncak Jaya in the Sudirman Range, 
<collectingRegion id="498231837C04CA69FEDDFD4B224CFCB1" box="[365,554,767,789]" country="Indonesia" name="Papua Barat" pageId="19" pageNumber="239">Papua Province</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F351BFF17C04CA69FD8CFD4B22D0FCB1" box="[572,694,767,789]" name="Indonesia" pageId="19" pageNumber="239">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C04CA69FF21FCAA2172FC96" authorityName="Slavenko &amp; Tamar &amp; Tallowin &amp; Kraus &amp; Allison &amp; Carranza &amp; Meiri" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Slavenko &amp; Tamar &amp; Tallowin &amp; Kraus &amp; Allison &amp; Carranza &amp; Meiri" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[145,276,797,819]" class="Squamata" family="Scincidae" genus="Nubeoscincus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Reptilia" pageId="19" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellaris">
<emphasis id="B93223737C04CA69FF21FCAA20C3FC97" box="[145,165,798,819]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="239">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B93223737C04CA69FF04FCA92172FC96" box="[180,276,797,818]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="239">stellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Star Mountains in 
<collectingRegion id="498231837C04CA69FDC3FCAA2092FCF6" country="Papua New Guinea" name="West Sepik" pageId="19" pageNumber="239">West Sepik Province</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F351BFF17C04CA69FEB2FC882185FCF6" box="[258,483,828,850]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="19" pageNumber="239">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
